# Garbage collection in one breath

## Reachable stays, the rest is reclaimed

- The GC tracks objects reachable from live code (locals, static fields) — you never `free`
- **Generational hypothesis**: most objects die young
- Heap split **young** ↔ **old**; survivors get **promoted** to old

## The three modern collectors

| Collector | Pause | Use case |
|---|---|---|
| `G1` | mostly short | default, general-purpose |
| `ZGC` | sub-ms | large heaps, low latency |
| `Shenandoah` | sub-ms | like ZGC, OpenJDK builds |

## Tuning

- Don't, unless forced — defaults are good; pick with `-XX:+UseZGC` etc. (G1 is default)
